apiDescription: RAII structure used to release the shared read access of a lock when dropped.
This structure is created by the read and try_read methods on RwLock.

trait implementations.name: impl<'a, T: ?std::marker::Sized + std::marker::Sync> std::marker::Sync for std::sync::RwLockReadGuard<'a, T>
impl<'a, T: std::fmt::Debug> std::fmt::Debug for std::sync::RwLockReadGuard<'a, T>
impl<'a, T: ?std::marker::Sized + std::fmt::Display> std::fmt::Display for std::sync::RwLockReadGuard<'a, T>
impl<'rwlock, T: ?std::marker::Sized> std::ops::Deref for std::sync::RwLockReadGuard<'rwlock, T>
impl<'a, T: ?std::marker::Sized> std::ops::Drop for std::sync::RwLockReadGuard<'a, T>
